  "prompt": "What is the dress code for fresher girls in Capgemini?",
  "response": "The dress code for fresher girls at Capgemini, as with most employees, generally adheres to a business casual standard. This typically means:\n\n1. **Tops**: Blouses, shirts, and smart tops. Avoid tops with bold logos or casual t-shirts.\n   \n2. **Bottoms**: Trousers, slacks, and skirts that are of appropriate length (typically knee-length or longer).\n\n3. **Dresses**: Business casual dresses that are not too short or too revealing.\n\n4. **Footwear**: Closed-toe shoes, flats, or modest heels. Avoid overly casual footwear like flip-flops.\n\n5. **Accessories**: Keep jewelry and accessories professional and not too extravagant.\n\n6. **Grooming**: Maintain a neat and professional appearance with well-groomed hair and minimal, natural makeup if you choose to wear it.\n\nIt's important to note that specific dress code requirements can vary depending on location, department, and the role you are hired for. It is always a good idea to confirm with HR or observe the norm in your specific office or team to ensure adherence to any specific guidelines.",
